cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on deep metric learning for image retrieval, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the importance of generalization and regularization, which are key concepts in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different layers in the deep metric learning system, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper demonstrates state-of-the-art performance on fine-grained image retrieval benchmarks, which could also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks such as text-based image retrieval.
